<title type="html"><![CDATA[XHTML: how to add char entities using DOCTYPE]]></title>

<content type="html" xml:base="https://forums.whatwg.org/bb3/viewtopic.php?t=4327&amp;p=5955#p5955"><![CDATA[
However, a better solution might be to not declare any entities and not use any entities. Don't escape the characters (except &lt; and &amp;), just include them directly. Or if you insist on escaping them, escape them using NCRs.<br /><br />...or use text/html where you can use entities without declaring them. <img src="https://forums.whatwg.org/bb3/images/smilies/icon_smile.gif" alt=":)" title="Smile" /><p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="https://forums.whatwg.org/bb3/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=4">zcorpan</a> — Tue Jun 15, 2010 9:56 am</p><hr />
]]></content>
