<title type="html"><![CDATA[XHTML: how to add char entities using DOCTYPE]]></title>

<content type="html" xml:base="https://forums.whatwg.org/bb3/viewtopic.php?t=4327&amp;p=5954#p5954"><![CDATA[
If you want to declare entities in the internal subset, then the simplest way is to omit the FPI and SI:<br /><br /><dl class="codebox"><dt>Code: </dt><dd><code>&lt;!DOCTYPE html &#91; &lt;!ENTITY foo &quot;bar&quot;&gt; &#93;&gt;</code></dd></dl><p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="https://forums.whatwg.org/bb3/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=4">zcorpan</a> — Tue Jun 15, 2010 9:54 am</p><hr />
]]></content>
